<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The macro LFS_UNLOCK(cfg) is defined as ((void)cfg), so the statement LFS_UNLOCK(lfs->cfg); only evaluates and discards the expression and has no effect on program state. Removing that statement would not change program behaviour in this build/configuration, therefore it is dead code and violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
</scenario>
